727
00:42:07,386 --> 00:42:10,506
The topic of my lecture today
is "Fact and Impact".

728
00:42:10,736 --> 00:42:14,106
It's also the secret of how MSC news took
number one spot in viewer ratings

729
00:42:14,386 --> 00:42:15,466
at its current air time.

730
00:42:15,816 --> 00:42:17,636
Since we have a lot
of reporters attending,

731
00:42:17,726 --> 00:42:22,276
let's put aside words like
coverage ethics or sense of duty

732
00:42:22,646 --> 00:42:25,156
and talk honestly and frankly.

733
00:42:25,246 --> 00:42:26,246
So arrogant.

734
00:42:29,166 --> 00:42:32,246
A reporter asked me
what kind of man I like.

735
00:42:32,406 --> 00:42:34,196
So I answered.

736
00:42:34,306 --> 00:42:36,596
I said, "I like a tall man."

737
00:42:39,266 --> 00:42:42,240
Next day that reporter
titled his news like this,

738
00:42:42,486 --> 00:42:45,376
"Reporter Song Cha-ok Likes A Tall Man."

739
00:42:45,946 --> 00:42:47,736
This is a news made with facts.

740
00:42:47,826 --> 00:42:49,126
It's not that interesting, right?

741
00:42:49,216 --> 00:42:50,216
Then...

742
00:42:51,166 --> 00:42:52,936
what if I changed it like this?

743
00:42:53,186 --> 00:42:55,626
"Reporter Song Cha-ok
Doesn't Like Short Men."

744
00:42:58,596 --> 00:43:03,086
If you look at these two headline, which
news would you be more attracted in?

745
00:43:03,176 --> 00:43:04,486
The second one.

746
00:43:05,516 --> 00:43:06,516
Yes.

747
00:43:06,946 --> 00:43:08,596
That's most people's characteristics.

748
00:43:08,776 --> 00:43:11,866
They're more attracted to stories that
attack someone rather than praising.

749
00:43:14,996 --> 00:43:17,636
But that doesn't mean
that the second one isn't fact.

750
00:43:17,746 --> 00:43:19,666
Because liking tall men means...

751
00:43:19,846 --> 00:43:23,416
that I don't like short men
compared to tall men.

752
00:43:24,106 --> 00:43:25,528
To grab the attention of the public,

753
00:43:25,619 --> 00:43:28,012
in news as well,
you have to add the impact

754
00:43:28,336 --> 00:43:29,346
to the fact, like this.

755
00:43:32,436 --> 00:43:34,046
An impact...

756
00:43:35,776 --> 00:43:37,386
She has a point.

757
00:43:38,006 --> 00:43:39,286
-Mr Director.
-Mr Director...

758
00:43:39,686 --> 00:43:41,176
Do you want to do that too?

759
00:43:42,306 --> 00:43:43,306
No.

760
00:43:43,656 --> 00:43:44,656
Okay.

761
00:43:44,746 --> 00:43:46,606
Now should we have another example?

762
00:43:46,956 --> 00:43:48,518
Some time ago,

763
00:43:48,609 --> 00:43:51,383
the police spread PR material saying
that the hit and run prosecution rate

764
00:43:51,474 --> 00:43:52,956
has broke through 93 percent.

765
00:43:53,186 --> 00:43:57,326
Each TV stations made news
with this PR material like this.

766
00:43:58,546 --> 00:43:59,656
Hit and Run Rate Almost 100%

767
00:43:59,746 --> 00:44:00,976
Hit and Run Rate Achieve 93%

768
00:44:01,816 --> 00:44:02,816
Hit and Run Rate Reach 93%

769
00:44:06,086 --> 00:44:08,536
These news were made exactly
the same as PR material.

770
00:44:09,086 --> 00:44:11,086
Those news have neither taste,
nor attraction.

771
00:44:11,266 --> 00:44:12,266
What the...

772
00:44:13,196 --> 00:44:14,386
Hold it. Hold it. Hold it.

773
00:44:14,476 --> 00:44:16,326
Let's just listen.

774
00:44:16,566 --> 00:44:18,826
She captured him with eyes closed
on purpose.

775
00:44:19,266 --> 00:44:20,976
-She's a completely annoying.
-Okay.

776
00:44:21,596 --> 00:44:26,176
Then, how would you make the title
if you want to make an impact?

777
00:44:26,716 --> 00:44:29,816
Unprosecuted hit and run cases
are over seven percent?

778
00:44:33,686 --> 00:44:34,876
Yes. That's a good start.

779
00:44:35,966 --> 00:44:39,976
By changing the idea a little like this,
it can become news with more impact.

780
00:44:40,136 --> 00:44:43,316
It set you apart from other stations and
it also has an effect of an exclusive.

781
00:44:43,696 --> 00:44:44,796
This news actually

782
00:44:44,886 --> 00:44:49,426
had higher viewers rating than other
hit and run prosecution rate news.

783
00:45:01,796 --> 00:45:03,506
I think he's going to take the highway.

